Hannah Beachler, who won the Oscar for Production Design for Black Panther, has advice for other young black girls who want to work in film production: “Don’t ever let anybody tell you you can’t do this craft. You are worthy and you are beautiful and this is something for you.”

“Finally the door is wide open and I’ve been struggling and digging deep and mentoring and doing whatever I could to raise others up, and I hope through my example this means that there is hope and other people can come on in and win an Oscar just like I did.” —Ruth Carter

Ruth Carter backstage at the #Oscars2019 : "I dreamed of this night. I dreamed of this night and I prayed for this night, honestly, not only just for being a hard-working costume designer but what it would mean for young people coming behind me.”

"This movement has allowed us and has inspired us to say, ‘No, I am supposed to have a seat at that table.’ That energy was going on throughout the production of the film. Barry [Jenkins] supported that and lifted it up as well." —Regina King at the #Oscars2019
